column3:
Thanks

BTW for next time: you don't need to open a new pull request after rebasing or making changes, you can push to the same branch on github and it will appear in the old pull.

Automatic sanity-testing: PASSED, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/f5f157b83fdcf4f70c40f47a5001d3e37dbb384a for binaries and test log.\nThis test script verifies pulls every time they are updated. It, however, dies sometimes and fails to test properly.  If you are waiting on a test, please check timestamps to verify that the test.log is moving at http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/cu
